manifest_findings.title:
Broadcast Receiver (androidx.profileinstaller.ProfileInstallReceiver) is Protected by a permission, but the protection level of the permission should be checked.
Permission: android.permission.DUMP
[android:exported=true]
manifest_findings.description: A Broadcast Receiver is found to be shared with other apps on the device therefore leaving it accessible to any other application on the device. It is protected by a permission which is not defined in the analysed application. As a result, the protection level of the permission should be checked where it is defined. If it is set to normal or dangerous, a malicious application can request and obtain the permission and interact with the component. If it is set to signature, only applications signed with the same certificate can obtain the permission.
manifest_findings.name: Broadcast Receiver androidx.profileinstaller.ProfileInstallReceiver is Protected by a permission, but the protection level of the permission should be checked. [Permission: android.permission.DUMP] [android:exported=true]

metadata.cwe: CWE-312: Cleartext Storage of Sensitive Information
metadata.description: Files may contain hardcoded sensitive information like usernames, passwords, keys etc.

metadata.cwe: CWE-532: Insertion of Sensitive Information into Log File
metadata.description: The App logs information. Sensitive information should never be logged.

metadata.cwe: CWE-89: Improper Neutralization of Special Elements used in an SQL Command ('SQL Injection')
metadata.description: App uses SQLite Database and execute raw SQL query. Untrusted user input in raw SQL queries can cause SQL Injection. Also sensitive information should be encrypted and written to the database.

warning.title: Broadcast Receiver (androidx.profileinstaller.ProfileInstallReceiver) is Protected by a permission, but the protection level of the permission should be checked.
warning.description:
Permission: android.permission.DUMP [android:exported=true]
A Broadcast Receiver is found to be shared with other apps on the device therefore leaving it accessible to any other application on the device. It is protected by a permission which is not defined in the analysed application. As a result, the protection level of the permission should be checked where it is defined. If it is set to normal or dangerous, a malicious application can request and obtain the permission and interact with the component. If it is set to signature, only applications signed with the same certificate can obtain the permission.
